  "prompt": "How do I breathe properly whilst speaking to people so that I remain relaxed and not nervous?",
  "response": "Here are some breathing techniques to help you stay calm while speaking:\n\n1. Diaphragmatic breathing\n- Breathe deeply from your belly, not your chest\n- Place one hand on your stomach\n- Inhale slowly through your nose for 4 seconds\n- Exhale slowly through your mouth for 4 seconds\n- This helps reduce anxiety and stabilizes your voice\n\n2. Before speaking\n- Take a few deep breaths before starting a conversation\n- Pause and breathe if you feel nervous mid-conversation\n\n3. Breathing rhythm\n- Maintain a steady, controlled breathing pattern\n- Avoid shallow, rapid breathing\n- Pause naturally when speaking to take breaths\n\n4. Practice mindfulness\n- Focus on your breath\n- If you feel tense, consciously take slow, deep breaths\n- This helps center your mind and reduce nervousness\n\n5. Preparation techniques\n- Practice speaking in front of a mirror\n- Do breathing exercises before social interactions\n- Visualize yourself speaking confidently\n\n6. Additional tips\n- Stay hydrated\n- Practice good posture\n- Speak at a comfortable pace\n\nRegular practice of these techniques will help you develop more natural, relaxed breathing during conversations.",
